        "created_at": "2022-07-16T07:10:08.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Sat up late watching the Open and to quote Sam Torrance, this is \u2018magnificent\u2019.</p>\n<p>Plush, perfectly ripe dark plum fruit mixes it with a veritable rose garden. The palate is just so silky, complete and detailed despite the juiciness. This is about as good as Volnay gets.<br>\nOne advantage of having just completed stock take is that I find boxes of things that I have forgotten that I bought. So pleased I found this one.</p>\n<p>Finished up with a few single malts, Tomatin 21yo and Aultmore 21yo the stand outs, but they were no help to my golf this morning.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 5,
        "updated_at": "2022-08-15T21:14:27.053Z",
